2. (1) In these Regulations — 

“Act of 1875” means the Explosives Act 1875 (38 & 39 Vict.) c. 17; 

“Act of 2005” means the Safety, Health and Welfare at Work Act 2005 (No. 10 
of 2005); 

“ANBI” means a substance assigned for the time being as ammonium nitrate 
blasting intermediate in accordance with UN Recommendation 3375 (being one 
of the UN Recommendations); 

